latestPosts.caption: Fascism thrives when we shrink ourselves literally and figuratively. So every time you choose to eat, rest, take up space, speak your truth, or wear what makes you feel powerful, you’re fighting back. Loving your body in a world that profits off your self-hate? That’s rebellion. That’s resistance. That’s how we fight fascism today. 🫶🏼

Caring is cool. 

My heart aches for the families being torn apart under this administration. It’s time to wake up. Use your voice. Stand up for each other. Protect your neighbors. America is built on stolen land no one’s race makes them more deserving of safety, dignity, or freedom. If you believe otherwise, it’s time to look in the mirror. Just because it doesn’t directly impact you doesn’t mean you shouldn’t care. Pick up a history book WE ARE GOING BACKWARDS. I’ve lived in LA for four years now, and I’ve seen the beauty of diversity and the power of community. Do not be silent right now.
